-- West Ham Beats Blackpool 2-1 to Win Promotion to Premier League
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-05-19T15:53:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-19/west-ham-beats-blackpool-2-1-to-win-promotion-to-premier-league.html
West Ham defeated Blackpool 2-1 to
win promotion back to English soccer’s Premier League.  Ricardo Vaz Te’s goal in the 87th minute won the
Championship playoff final at Wembley Stadium in  London .  Carlton
Cole  also scored for West Ham and Thomas Ince had the Blackpool
goal.  West Ham’s victory is worth at least 90 million pounds
($142 million) in television rights and other financial payments
from the Premier League, accountant Deloitte LLP estimates. The
Hammers were relegated to the second tier last season after
finishing last in the Premier League.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  